<subSubSection pageId="188" pageNumber="950" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="188.[789,1382,1860,2288]" lastBlockId="188.[168,1381,2294,3472]" pageId="188" pageNumber="950">
Subgenus Chrysopteron. See 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1832" box="[1171,1305,1939,1972]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="188" pageNumber="950" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tricolor">M. tricolor</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" baseAuthorityYear="1835" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="188" pageNumber="950" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="formosus">Myotis formosus</taxonomicName>
was previously considered to include as races or synonyms M. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1923" box="[1269,1374,2018,2051]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="188" pageNumber="950" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hermani">hermani</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jentink" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[790,944,2062,2091]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="188" pageNumber="950" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bartelsii">M. bartelsii</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jentink" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[967,1099,2062,2091]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="188" pageNumber="950" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="weberi">M. weberi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Waterhouse" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[1122,1304,2062,2091]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="188" pageNumber="950" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufopictus">M. rufopictus</taxonomicName>
, and M. rufoniger, all now split based on morphology and genetics. Race flavus has been considered a separate species; the form watasei, likewise from 
<collectingCountry box="[1208,1309,2224,2249]" name="Taiwan" pageId="188" pageNumber="950">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, was also included in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[1045,1210,2255,2288]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="188" pageNumber="950" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="formosus">M. formosus</taxonomicName>
but is now considered a synonym of M. rufoniger;, the precise ranges of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[1019,1177,2294,2327]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="188" pageNumber="950" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="formosus">M. formosus</taxonomicName>
and M. rufoniger in south-east 
<collectingCountry box="[405,490,2334,2367]" name="China" pageId="188" pageNumber="950">China</collectingCountry>
require clarification. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
